MusicHelp.Command2: %P%music connect (Voice channel ID) - You can connect me to a voice channel. If you give no name or ID, I'll try to join to the same voice channel which you in
MusicHelp.Command3: %P%music play (YouTube link, remote file, where the URL ends with the extension, the query index or search patter in YouTube) - Starts playing the remote file, YouTube link, the query or starts to search, then plays it
MusicHelp.Command5: %P%music add [YouTube link, remote file, where the URL ends with the extension or the search pattern in YouTube] - Adds the YouTube video the remote file.
MusicHelp.Command6: %P%music remove [Query index] - Removes song from the query
MusicHelp.Command8: %P%music search [Response] - Cancels or selects from the search result
MusicHelp.Command9: %P%music next - If the query contains more items, then starts playing the next, otherwise it restarts the query.
MusicHelp.Command10: %P%music prev - If the query contains more items, then starts playing the previous, otherwise it restarts the query.
MusicHelp.Command12: %P%music pause - Pauses playing, if you want to continue, just type play with no parameteres
MusicHelp.Bottom: Property in '()' is optional, and in '[]' is required!```
